## Summary

Implemented T-012: Node Detail Panel with the following:

### Files Created
- **`src/types/stack.ts`** — Domain types for `StackNode`, `StackEdge`, `NodeCategory`, `NodeSubtype`, `ConnectionType`, `StackArchitecture` (prerequisite for T-004)
- **`src/lib/node-config.ts`** — Category/subtype config with display names, colors, and lucide-react icon mappings
- **`src/components/canvas/NodeDetailPanel.tsx`** — Slide-out detail panel with:
  - Editable name, technology, description fields
  - Category dropdown (changes subtype options and resets to first subtype)
  - Subtype dropdown (filtered by selected category)
  - Read-only AI reasoning section
  - Lock/unlock toggle switch
  - Two-click delete confirmation
  - Outside-click-to-close behavior
  - Animated slide-in/out via CSS transition
- **`src/components/canvas/NodeDetailPanel.test.tsx`** — 15 component tests

### Files Modified
- **`src/app/project/[id]/page.tsx`** — Integrated panel with `selectedNode` state, `handleNodeUpdate`, `handleNodeDelete`, `handleClosePanel` callbacks
- **`src/test/setup.ts`** — Added explicit cleanup for proper test isolation
- **`package.json`** — Added `lucide-react` dependency

### Key Learnings
- `@testing-library/react` auto-cleanup requires `globals: true` in vitest — add explicit `cleanup()` instead
- lucide-react dynamic icon access needs `unknown` intermediate cast
- ESLint `react-hooks/static-components` requires wrapper components for dynamic icon resolution
